shootings: Authorities are increasingly on the defensive about
their actions or non-response to warnings about Eric Harris's
threats. Other developments. By James Brooke.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   COLO-SCHOOL-BACKLASH (Boston) _ Teen-agers dressed in black and
regular outcasts report a backlash against them. Both peers and
parents are snitching on them; computers are being taken away,
other teens shun them even more. One 18 year old senior in
California, who dresses Goth, said that other kids now look at him
and say ``Oh, are you going to come to school and shoot us all up
or what?'' Even his mom, who has been understanding of his dress
asked: ``What is the difference between you and them?'' The answer
from the kid: ``I haven't killed anyone yet.'' By Carey Goldberg.
</P>
<P>
   COLO-SCHOOL-CLINTON (Washington) _ With its plan for a White
House meeting on media violence, the administration continues its
effort to navigate the currents of public opinion on school
shooting in Colorado. By John M. Broder.
</P>
