   OLYMPICS
</P>
<P>
   OLY-ATLANTARECORDS _ ATLANTA _ Nearly three years after the
Atlanta Olympics, a small portion of ACOG'S records are made
available Friday to the public. The Atlanta Journal-Constitution,
which has fought to see the files under the Georgia Open Records
Act, gets a glimpse of up to nine boxes. (Turner, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
