   &UR; OTHER CULTURE AND ENTERTAINMENT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   TV-ARK-REVIEW (Undated) _ Sunday on NBC, the opening episode of
``Noah's Ark,'' a six-hour mini-series. Reviewed by Anita Gates.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SPORTS &LR;  (``s'' code)
</P>
<P>
   FBN-RHODEN-COLUMN (Undated) _ Sports of The Times column on
Terrell Davis, the Broncos star running back, who in the wake of
John Elway's retirement, has taken up a new sport: bowling. With
Bubby Brister and not Elway at quarterback for Denver, Davis will
likely become even more of a workhorse for the Super Bowl
championship team. By William C. Rhoden.
</P>
