George W. Bush is taking a $169,400 political ``payoff'' from
industrial polluters for his presidential campaign while the
Legislature considers new curbs on pollution. Under state law, Bush
would not be able to take campaign contributions while lawmakers
are in regular session, but the state law doesn't apply to a
federal campaign. By R.G. RATCLIFFE.
</P>
