<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are the business news stories the Los Angeles Daily News
plans to move for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs
of Saturday, May 1, and thereafter. The stories will carry the
``f'' financial news category code unless otherwise noted. For
questions about stories, contact Susan Leh at the Daily News, (818)
713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   NEWCOM-ACTIVITY (Los Angeles) _ NewCom Inc. is apparently the
latest micro-cap company to get caught up in Internet hype. On
Thursday, shares of the Westlake Village-based company increased 93
percent on 1.2 million shares traded to 63.75 cents. By midday
Friday, those shares were down 15 percent on 600,000 shares traded
to 56.75 cents. Normally, only 170,000 shares trade daily. By Ben
Sullivan. (Will move in the ``f'' financial news file.)
</P>
<P>
   MODEL-SCULPTURES (Los Angeles) _ Rijn &AMP; Reisman, a tiny
7-year-old North Hollywood company creating sculptures for movies
and theme parks, has completed its largest project ever by cranking
out dozens of the characters used at Universal Studios' upcoming
Islands of Adventure. By Dave McNary. (Will move in the ``f''
financial news file.)
</P>
