<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CLARIFICATION-CANADA-SOCIETY-BOS </SLUG>
  
 (Eds.: Newspapers that used the Boston Globe story CANADA-SOCIETY
(s) by Colin Nickerson, which moved Thursday for Friday A.M. use,
will wish to use the following clarification.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Homicide statistics in a Boston Globe story about a school
shooting in Taber, Canada, may have been misleading. The US
homicide rate in 1997 was 6.8 per 100,000 population, about 3.6
times the Canadian rate of 1.92 per 100,000. In absolute numbers,
there were 18,209 homicides in the United States in 1997, according
to FBI statistics, more than 30 times the Canadian total of 587.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; The Boston Globe &LR;  &QC;
