building a $50 million factory in this town outside St. Petersburg
when, one day last August, the Russian financial system collapsed,
seemingly confirming the worst corporate fears about Russia. Some
companies pulled out, and many that had considered entering Russia
shelved their plans. But Caterpillar and a number of Western
multinationals are coping with Russia's economic crisis by settling
deeper into Russia rather than pulling out. By Neela Banerjee.
