<P>
   POW-MEETING (Los Angeles) _ Vivian Ramirez hung on the Rev.
Jesse Jackson's every word as he describes his visit with her son,
prisoner of war Andrew Ramirez, and the two others. By Peter
Hartlaub and Lisa Van Proyen.(Will move in the ``n'' California and
``a'' national news files.)
</P>
<P>
   134-5-CONNECTOR (Los Angeles) _ Burbank city staff says Caltrans
restrictions boost the cost of connecting the 5 and 134 freeways by
millions of dollars, making the improvement difficult to justify.
Staff said a second examination is needed, but city officials say
they are prepared to lobby Caltrans do waive its rules so the
missing links can be built. By Lee Condon. (Will move in the ``n''
California news file.)
</P>
<P>
   GAS-OUT (Los Angeles) _ Gas stations were fairly empty as
motorists protested the high price of gasoline by mounting a
boycott, the Great Gas-Out. By Phillip W. Browne. (Will move in the
``n'' California and ``a'' national news files.)
</P>
<P>
   RUMORS-VIOLENCE (Los Angeles) _ Nearly 650 students stayed home
from Granada Hills High School because of Colorado-shooting rumors
that something bad would happen Friday. Nothing did, although an
eery silence hung over the school with so many youngsters gone. By
Jesse Hiestand. (Will move in the ``n'' California and ``a''
national news files.)
</P>
<P>
   PAULY-PRINCIPAL (Los Angeles) _ Canoga Park High School students
kept calling their pricipal ``weasel'' all day Friday, and not one
got in trouble for it. Their principal for the day was actor and
comedian Pauly Shore. By Steve Carney. (Will move in the ``n''
California, ``a'' national and ``e'' entertainment news files.)
</P>
