<HEADLINE>
WHERE TO TURN FOR MORE RADIO DRAMA, `STAR WARS' 
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients)  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Check out the ``Star Wars'' page on the Daily News
Web site (www.dailynews.com). It will continually be updated with
new information during the countdown to ``Star Wars: Episode 1 _
The Phantom Menace.'' You can also hear snippets from some of the
radio dramas as well as link to related sites. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   There are some 50 audio adaptations of secondary ``Star Wars''
novels. Most are performed by a single reader, but a number of
entertaining full-scale dramas have been produced (some locally at
West Valley Studios in Chatsworth):
</P>
<P>
   ``Dark Empire I, II, III'' _ Luke goes bad and Emperor Palpatine
(or at least his clone) returns from the dead to trouble the Rebel
Alliance.
</P>
<P>
   ``Tales of the Jedi/Dark Lords of the Sith'' _ Concerns events
that took place thousands of years before the present film cycle.
</P>
<P>
   ``Dark Forces I, II, III'' _ The view from the other side with
the adventures of an Imperial officer.
</P>
<P>
   ``Tales From the Mos Eisley Cantina I, II'' _ how did that
motley assortment of aliens wind up at that disreputable Tatooine
bar?
</P>
<P>
   ``Crimson Empire'' _ Remember the Emperor's guards, the guys in
red? &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   KCRW (89.9) airs plays from L.A. Theatre Works at 6 p.m.
Sundays. This month's plays:
</P>
<P>
   ``The Colored Museum'' (tonight), ``The Odd Couple'' with Nathan
Lane and David Paymer (May 9), ``Working'' (May 16), ``Anna
Christie'' (May 23), ``After the Fall'' with Anthony La Paglia (May
30).
</P>
<P>
   The station also airs ``Selected Shorts'' at 7 p.m. Saturdays.
Readers of short stories this month include Paul Reiser, Leonard
Nimoy and Jane Curtin. &QL; 
