<SLUG> BC-FBC-UCLANOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NO SUMMER VACATION FOR UCLA QUARTERBACKS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JON WILNER  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ UCLA concludes spring football practice with a
scrimmage today at Spaulding Field that may answer a few lingering
questions but will not determine a starting quarterback.
</P>
<P>
   For that, coach Bob Toledo will wait until training camp.
</P>
<P>
   None of the competitors _ junior Drew Bennett, sophomore Scott
McEwan, redshirt freshmen Cory Paus and Ryan McCann, and true
freshman J.P. Losman _ has dominated play, although each has
performed well in stretches.
</P>
<P>
   ``They've all made progress, but I want to see how hard they
work in the summer,'' Toledo said. ``If I make a decision, some of
them might not work as hard.''
</P>
<P>
   As they've done in scrimmages throughout the spring, the
quarterbacks will shed their protective red jerseys today and
become live targets _ enabling Toledo and offensive coordinator Al
Borges to evaluate them under pressure.
</P>
<P>
   Other intriguing personnel questions include safety, where Eric
Whitfield and Audie Attar are competing to play alongside Jason
Stephens, and outside linebacker, where Billy Pieper and Ali
Abdul-Azziz have traded time with the starting defense.
</P>
<P>
   Odds and ends: The Bruins will have a short practice at 1 p.m.
and then start the scrimmage at approximately 1:30. It is open to
the public. Afterward, the Bruins will host an invitation-only
barbecue for football alumni and family.... Receiver Danny Farmer,
who practiced only three days because of his volleyball commitment,
will not participate in the scrimmage. Farmer and defensive lineman
Pete Holland have been voted captains for the 1999 season.... The
Bruins are 600 season tickets ahead of last year's record pace.
</P>
</TEXT>
