u a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-COLO-SCHOOL-WEBSITE-N     04-30 0696
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-COLO-SCHOOL-WEBSITE-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ON THE WEB, WARNINGS FROM STUDENT WHO BECAME SLAYER 
</HEADLINE>
   (bl)  
 By JAMES BARRON    c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   The printout of material from Eric Harris' Web site released
Friday was a hodgepodge of rantings about Denver (``I would love to
kill almost all of its residents'') and things he loved and hated
(school was in the first category, schoolwork in the second).
</P>
<P>
   The printout was made public by the Jefferson County Sheriff's
Department, which said it had received it 13 months ago from Randy
Brooks Brown, the father of a classmate of Harris at Columbine High
School in Littleton, Colo., a suburb of Denver. Brown had
complained that Harris had made death threats to his son.
</P>
<P>
   Since Harris and his friend Dylan Klebold killed 13 people and
themselves at Columbine High School last week, Brown has criticized
the sheriff's department for not doing enough about his complaints.
He has also distributed much of the material the department
released Friday. It is laced with expletives.
</P>
<P>
   ``These are the words of wisdom from Reb,'' Harris declared at
one point, using a name he used on America Online.
</P>
<P>
   ``For those of you who happen to know me and know that I respect
you, may peace be with you and don't be in my line of fire,'' he
wrote. Others, he warned, should ``hide in your houses because I'm
comin for EVERYONE soon, and i WILL be armed.''
</P>
<P>
   ``I WILL shoot to kill,'' Harris added, saying he would ``KILL
EVERYTHING.''
</P>
<P>
   ``No, I am not crazy,'' he said. ``Crazy is just a word, to me
it has no meaning.''
</P>
<P>
   In one of the more intriguing passages, Harris, whom officials
said targeted blacks in his attack at the school, repeatedly asked
readers of the site, ``You know what I hate?'' One of the answers
he gave was, ``RACISM!''
</P>
<P>
   He wrote that people who are biased against ``blacks, Asians,
Mexicans or people from any other country or race besides
white-American'' should ``have their arms ripped off'' and be
burned.
</P>
<P>
   ``Don't let me catch you making fun of someone just because they
are a different color,'' he wrote.
</P>
<P>
   The printout also indicated that Harris had given names to pipe
bombs he had made. He described the detonation of one bomb that he
called Pazzie as ``a complete success.'' He said that it had been
set off in a creek bed and that the explosion had been
``heart-pounding, gut-wrenching, brain-twichin, (sic)
ground-moving, insanely cool.''
</P>
<P>
   At another point, in a section headed ``philosophy,'' Harris
wrote: ``My belief is that if I say something, it goes. I am the
law. If you don't like it, you die. If I don't like you or I don't
like what you want me to do, you die.''
</P>
<P>
   He added, ``Dead people can't do many things, like argue.''
</P>
<P>
   In another section of the transcript, Harris repeatedly asked,
``You know what I hate?'' His answers ranged from fans of ``Star
Wars'' to people who pronounce words ``like ofTen, or acrosT, or
eXpreso,'' and added, ``Learn to speak correctly, you morons.''
</P>
<P>
   He also wrote that he hated country music, freedom of the press
and opponents of the death penalty. He said the courts should ``fry
conficts (sic) even if all they did was unarmed robbery!''
</P>
<P>
   The transcript was a mishmash of sometimes conflicting
observations. Harris said that he loved Zippo lighters, for
example, but hated ``young smokers.''
</P>
<P>
   ``They think they are so goddamn cool with their big bad
ciggarettes and their `sooo cool' attitude,'' he wrote. ``I can't
wait until they are about 25,'' he said, and have to ``talk with a
computer hooked up to their X-vocal cords.''
</P>
<P>
   He also complained about ``liars.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Oh gawwwwwd I hate liars,'' Harris wrote, saying his
neighborhood had ``thousands of them.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Why must people lie so damn much! Especially about stupid
things! Like, `Yeah, I just bought 5 cases of M-80's in Oklahoma
for about $5. And they are legal there and everything. Yeah, my
parents buy most of my guns, every once in a while I'll use my
4,000 dollar paycheck and buy a shotgun or 2.'''
</P>
<P>
   But in speaking about his own explosives, he wrote, ``Now our
only problem is to find the place that will be `ground zero.'''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
